    "long_instructions": "# Changing Sprites\r\n\r\nThis program uses the [`keyDown()`(#fff176)](/docs/ide/gamelab/expressions/keyDown) block to detect whether a specific keys are being pressed down.\r\n\r\n# Do This\r\n1) Run the code and try pressing the \"p\" and \"h\" keys.\r\n2) Look inside the first two conditional statements to see how the code works.\r\n3) Add code to change the sprite to a different animal when the \"r\" key is pressed.\r\n   - Add a [`setAnimation()`(#f78183)](/docs/ide/gamelab/expressions/setAnimation) block inside the 3rd [`if ()`(#64B5F6)](/docs/ide/gamelab/expressions/ifBlock) statement.\r\n   - Set the animation to the rabbit.",
